112
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,400
I'm looking for Liu Fenfang.

113
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:52,409
What for?

114
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,570
Are you Liu Fenfang?

115
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,020
So what if I am?

116
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,000
Never mind.

117
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Stop right there.

118
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,090
I'm Liu Fenfang.

119
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:05,430
You're looking for me?

120
00:08:29,930 --> 00:08:31,260
My name is Du Xiangdong.

121
00:08:31,930 --> 00:08:34,130
You were introduced by Chief Li, right?

122
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,000
Wait a moment.

123
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,200
This young man looks so handsome,

124
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,480
like a movie star.

125
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,290
He's not bad.

126
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,700
Is there something wrong with your eyes?

127
00:09:12,290 --> 00:09:14,350
No. These are just for windproofing.

128
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,770
It took me three hours to bike here.

129
00:09:19,230 --> 00:09:20,630
He barely passed.

130
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:22,030
His height is okay.

131
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,530
Hey, young man,

132
00:09:24,930 --> 00:09:25,800
why didn't you find a restaurant

133
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,370
for the blind date?

134
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:30,130
I saw a noodle shop at the factory gate on my way here.

135
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:31,330
How about we go there?

136
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,190
Noodle shop sounds good.

137
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,050
He's quite stingy.

138
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:39,050
You might want to reconsider.

139
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:40,980
I think he's quite down-to-earth.

140
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,680
Life is about practicality.

141
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,970
Do you like watching plays?

142
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,080
When I was in police academy,

143
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:10,550
I was in the drama club.

144
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:11,320
Really?

145
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:14,060
What roles have you played?

146
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,700
I was in charge of printing the programs.

147
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,940
I don't have anything to do after work today.

148
00:10:25,230 --> 00:10:26,690
I just came here to see you.

149
00:10:26,930 --> 00:10:28,800
I have to rush back to the center for duty.

150
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:31,130
I'll have to bike for another three hours.

151
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:35,530
Well...

152
00:10:37,180 --> 00:10:38,410
you should head back now.

153
00:10:38,410 --> 00:10:40,410
It's not safe to ride a bike at night.

154
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,260
Alright, I'll be off then.

155
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,840
Why haven't you left yet?

156
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,460
Can we see each other again in the future?

157
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:39,350
[Inspection and stamping]

158
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:33,990
Turn around.

159
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,440
Turn around.

160
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:52,580
Qualified pork.

161
00:11:53,660 --> 00:11:54,940
Don't talk nonsense.

162
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,520
This is proof of love.

163
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,880
It shows that the girl recognizes him.

164
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,360
Du, go for it.

165
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:01,530
I've got your back.

166
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,440
Why did you come back so soon?

167
00:12:03,770 --> 00:12:04,650
Yeah.

168
00:12:05,190 --> 00:12:06,900
That was way too short.

169
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,030
I've already requested leave for you.

170
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:09,320
You didn't even need to go back tonight.

171
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,300
He doesn't even know how to deal with a girl.

172
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:12,250
Even if you gave him a whole evening, he wouldn't know what to do.

173
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:13,050
Is it all gone?

174
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,290
Yes.

175
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,420
Where's Chief?

176
00:12:18,290 --> 00:12:19,620
What do you need him for?

177
00:12:20,590 --> 00:12:21,790
What else could it be?

178
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:23,180
He promised me.

179
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,890
He should keep his word.

180
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:26,150
You're doing it again.

181
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:28,000
Why are you so stubborn?

182
00:12:28,370 --> 00:12:29,890
I'm not trying to criticize you.

183
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:32,090
But Chief just introduced you to a girl.

184
00:12:32,930 --> 00:12:33,770
I advise you

185
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:35,080
not to make a fool of yourself.

186
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,650
Otherwise, Chief might teach you a lesson.

187
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:38,780
Who knows who will teach whom a lesson?

188
00:12:39,770 --> 00:12:41,370
I've made up my mind this time.

189
00:12:41,370 --> 00:12:42,830
No one can talk me out of it.

190
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:44,480
You're acting tough, huh?

191
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,080
Also,

192
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,550
you can take whatever you want

193
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,200
from these things in my room.

194
00:12:49,610 --> 00:12:50,670
You're not going to take any of these things with you?

195
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,400
Except for that tape recorder.

196
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:56,150
What a waste of words.

197
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,600
Fatty San!

198
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,250
Fatty San!

199
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:06,200
Come out and buy fish!

200
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:10,220
Fatty San! Come out and buy fish!

201
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,810
What should we do, Boss?

202
00:13:13,770 --> 00:13:14,720
Report it to the police.

203
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,010
Report it to the police.

204
00:13:16,010 --> 00:13:17,340
Report it to the police!

205
